sentences.english: Joseph draws such that flowers and plants and landscape painting have the standard suitable.
sentences.chinese: 約瑟夫畫得花卉與風景畫具有相當水準。

sentences.english: And Joseph went throughout the land of Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 約瑟就出去巡行埃及地。

sentences.english: And he put them all in custody for three days.
sentences.chinese: 於是約瑟把他們都下在監裏三天。

sentences.english: He said to his brothers, "Listen to this dream I had."
sentences.chinese: 爲了這個夢，約瑟的哥哥們恨透了他。

sentences.english: So Manasseh and Ephraim, the descendants of Joseph, received their inheritance.
sentences.chinese: 約瑟的兒子瑪拿西，以法蓮就得了他們的地業。

sentences.english: Yet did not the chief butler remember Joseph, but forgat him.
sentences.chinese: 酒政卻不記念約瑟，竟忘了他。

sentences.english: And Joseph's ten brethren went down to buy corn in Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 於是，約瑟的十個哥哥都下埃及糴糧去了。

sentences.english: Vinegar-faced Joseph projected his head from a round window of the barn.
sentences.chinese: 苦臉的約瑟夫從穀倉的一個圓窗裏探出頭來。

sentences.english: Joseph turned to her and took her hands.
sentences.chinese: 約瑟夫把臉轉向她，拉起她的手。

sentences.english: Joseph says it's a high-crime area. That's why they have three pit bulls, all named "Peaches."
sentences.chinese: 約瑟夫說，這是一個高犯罪率的地區。

sentences.english: When Reuben returned to the cistern and saw that Joseph was not there, he tore his clothes.
sentences.chinese: 流便回到坑邊，見約瑟不在坑裏，就撕裂衣服。

sentences.english: The papers that make it legal were signed at the time of the arrangement of the marriage.
sentences.chinese: 馬利亞和約瑟的婚書已在安排婚約時簽署。

sentences.english: What have you learned from Joseph's dealing in Potiphar's wife incidence?
sentences.chinese: 你從約瑟于波提乏之妻事件中的表現學到什麼？

sentences.english: Joseph had the power to destroy his jealous and envious and mean brothers.
sentences.chinese: 約瑟有權力處置他那些充滿嫉妒和卑劣手段的哥哥們。

sentences.english: And Joseph was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh king of Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 約瑟見埃及王法老的時候年三十歲。
